'description': "Project Topic- Role of the Geo-Drilling Event(GDE) and Hydrocarbon Shows(HCS) Databases in Geothermal Well Planning
The project involved analysis of 40 gas wells in the prospective geothermal areas. The analysis was done in the two databases., GDE and HCS. GDE database suggested the expected geo drilling events in the prospective area of exploration and HCS database suggested the areas where high gas peaks can be expected. A synergy test was done between the two database giving indication of 'Gain' hazards (in GDE DB) associated with high gas peaks( in HCS DB).", 'title': 'Intern', 'employment_type': None}, {'location': 'Utrecht Area, Netherlands', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'company': 'EBN B.V.', 'description': "Project topic- An investigation of field parameters controlling Induced Seismicity.
The term 'Induced seismicity' in the Netherlands brings the name of Groningen gas field is everyones mind. For my project, I take a step further to see the behaviour of small fields and seismicity experienced by them. Geological and Reservoir parameters were looked into and analysed in Spotfire for this purpose. I made a database in Spotfire for 67 fields in the Netherlands. In future, more fields are to be added in this database. Further, Empirical modelling for prediction then was used for the most seismicaly active fields. Fault characterisation was used to support the modelling. 
Key skills learned during the project- Sportfire, QGIS, Petrel", 'title': 'Research Intern', 'employment_type': None}]}]
volunteer_experiences: [{'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'role': 'Hydrogeologist Intern', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'ACWADAM', 'logo': None, 'url': None}, 'cause': 'SCIENCE_AND_TECHNOLOGY', 'description': 'Worked with a team of geologist to study the distribution of groundwater in different villages of Jharkhand state in India. The study mainly comprised of confined aquifers with respect to the underlying geology. This study was carried out to come up with a plan to fight the water shortage faced by the residents during summer season. My work also included carrying out infiltration test study in paddy fields which becomes after the monsoon season becomes unusable. This was done to test a new breed of rice which does not require water flooding. The major aim of fieldwork was to increase awareness about good agriculture practices among the farmers.'}]
